-- Mazda Falls in Tokyo Trading After Nikkei Reports Ford to Reduce Stake
-- B y   I a n   R o w l e y
-- 2010-10-18T00:02:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/mazda-falls-in-tokyo-trading-after-nikkei-reports-ford-to-reduce-stake.html
Mazda Motor Corp. fell 3.3 percent
to 207 yen as of 9 a.m. in Tokyo trading after Nikkei English
News reported Ford Motor Co. may reduce its stake in the
Japanese automaker.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Rowley in Tokyo at 
